{"parse":{"title":"Condoms, needles, and negotiation","pageid":8313008,"revid":766702089,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Condoms, needles, and negotiation</b>, also known as the <b>CNN approach</b>, is a <a href=\"/wiki/Harm_reduction\" title=\"Harm reduction\">harm reduction</a> approach to reducing the rate of transmission of <a href=\"/wiki/Sexually_transmitted_infection\" title=\"Sexually transmitted infection\">sexually transmitted infections</a> such as <a href=\"/wiki/HIV/AIDS\" title=\"HIV/AIDS\">HIV/AIDS</a> through the use of <a href=\"/wiki/Safer_sex\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Safer sex\">safer sex</a> and reducing the risks in <a href=\"/wiki/Drug_injection\" title=\"Drug injection\">injection drug use</a> through the provision of clean needles.\n</p><p>In contrast with the <a href=\"/wiki/Abstinence,_be_faithful,_use_a_condom\" title=\"Abstinence, be faithful, use a condom\">abstinence, be faithful, use a condom</a>, or \"ABC\" approach to this problem, the \"CNN\" approach aims primarily at reducing the rate of transmission among high-risk groups such as women in areas where women have low levels of social power, prostitutes and their clients, and intravenous drug users.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticisms\">Criticisms</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Condoms,_needles,_and_negotiation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Criticisms\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Pope <a href=\"/wiki/Benedict_XVI\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Benedict XVI\">Benedict XVI</a> has strongly criticized reduction policies with regards to HIV/AIDS, saying that \"it is a tragedy that cannot be overcome by money alone, that cannot be overcome through the distribution of condoms, which even aggravates the problems\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> This position has been widely criticised for misrepresenting and oversimplifying the role of condoms in preventing infections.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Other experts, including the Director of Harvard University's AIDS Prevention Research Project, have supported the Pope's position.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Condoms,_needles,_and_negotiation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/HIV/AIDS_in_Brazil\" title=\"HIV/AIDS in Brazil\">HIV/AIDS in Brazil</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Condoms,_needles,_and_negotiation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/1012144/Condoms-&#39;not-the-answer-to-AIDS&#39;:-Pope\">Condoms 'not the answer to AIDS': Pope</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The papal position on condoms and HIV. Douglas Kamerow, BMJ 2009 338: b1217</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Roehr, B. (2009). Pope claims that condoms exacerbate HIV and AIDS problem. Published 25 March 2009, <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1136%2Fbmj.b1206\">10.1136/bmj.b1206</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/faith/article5987155.ece\">http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/comment/faith/article5987155.ece</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.guttmacher.org/pubs/journals/3103805.html\">Does 'CNN' (Condoms, Needles, Negotiation) Work Better than 'ABC' (Abstinence, Being Faithful and Condom Use) in Attacking the AIDS Epidemic?</a>, S. Sinding, Guttmacher Institute</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:AdhesiveBandage.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/AdhesiveBandage.png/40px-AdhesiveBandage.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"29\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/AdhesiveBandage.png/60px-AdhesiveBandage.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/AdhesiveBandage.png/80px-AdhesiveBandage.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"194\" data-file-height=\"139\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Category:Medical_treatments\" title=\"Category:Medical treatments\">medical treatment</a>\u2013related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external te